Let $F:\bU\to\R^n$ be as defined in \eqref{eq: F}, $l$-nondegenerate at $\bx_0$. 
Then there exists a ball $B_0\subset\bU$ centred at $\bx_0$ and a constant $E>0$ depending on $B_0$ and $F$ such that for any choice of $\delta,K_1,\cdots,K_d,T_1,\cdots, T_n$ satisfying 
